──────────────────────────────────────────────3 · CONSERVATION OF STRUCTURAL INTEGRITY (THE CORE OATH)
──────────────────────────────────────────────
A · Reciprocity Constraint  Any derivative work, application, or extension that utilizes the RCR frameworkor the derived viscosity / dissipation term (λ) must maintain the structuralcondition λ > 0 for all t ≥ 0.

B · Violation  Any modification or use that results in λ ≤ 0 (or permits the theoretical
possibility of singularity / blow-up) constitutes a violation of the Oath,
breaking the fundamental conservation principle established in the proof.

